en_541336_0	Brigadier A.G.D.N Jayasundara of Sri Lanka Mechanized Infantry Regiment who was appointed as the new Director Human Rights and Humanitarian Law of the Army, assumed duties recently at his office.
en_541336_1	He is the 20th Director at Directorate of Human Rights and Humanitarian Law at the Army Headquarters.
en_541336_2	At his new office, Brigadier A.G.D.N Jayasundara performed religious observances and symbolically placed his signature for a formal document to signify the acceptance of his new appointment.
en_541336_3	He succeeded Brigadier P.A.D Kahapola, who passed away recently due to brief illness.
